The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Govt signs resort pact
                                                                                                               Govt signs resort pact
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, Feb. 28: The Mahindra group today signed an agreement with the government to set up a string of holiday resorts across the state.         
	In the first phase of the project, Mahindra Holidays and Resorts India Ltd will build five resorts in Jaldapara, Garumara, Mandarmoni, Darjeeling and the Sunderbans at Rs 200 crore. The company will need 10 to 20 acres for each resort, which will have 100-150 rooms.        
	The project will kick off with a world-class resort in the Sunderbans, probably in December this year, company chairman Arun Nanda said.        
	Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee was present when the pact was inked at Writers Buildings today.                                                                                                                                                                              
